parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tires can lead to a loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Cracking on the sidewall of the tires
sudden blowouts
shredding of the tire tread
loss of tire pressure
and difficulty controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper installation of the wiring harness can cause the vehicle to stall randomly, leading to a loss of power and potential accidents. Additionally, it can short out the alternator and starter, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls randomly
the alternator fails
the starter fails
the wiring harness is damaged or melted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the engine dies while driving
loss of power while accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the side mirror glass can cause a distraction to the driver, potentially leading to an accident. Additionally, the broken glass can cause injury to passengers or bystanders.
symptoms: The side mirror glass falls out of the mirror housing
the side mirror glass breaks or shatters
the mirror glass is loose or unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door trim and molding can cause loose parts to detach and become projectiles, potentially causing injury or distraction to the driver.
symptoms: The plastic molding on the door is loose or coming off
the door trim is cracked or broken
the door trim is not securely attached.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line Failure Due to Chassis Rubbing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake line can cause a sudden loss of brake fluid, leading to a complete loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brake function
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake warning light illuminates on the dashboard
brake fluid leakage under the vehicle.
